SIMPLE: cheerless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cheerless
<hw>Cheer"less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Without joy, gladness, or
comfort.</def></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Cheer"less*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Cheer"less*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My cheerful day is turned to <qex>cheerless</qex> night.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Gloomy; sad; comfortless; dispiriting;
disconsolate; dejected; melancholy; forlorn.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cheerly</ent>⟦br⟧
